Bochum, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 51.481846, 7.216236.

Bochum is a large city in western Germany, in the province of North Rhine-Westphalia, in highly populated metropolitan area of Dusseldorf, Essen, Dortmund, Wuppertal, and Cologne. There are about 370,000 people live in the city, making it on the list of 20 most populated cities in Germany. It is a key social and cultural center of the area, with plenty of theaters, concert halls, exhibition centers, shopping areas, etc. Local tourist attractions include the Old Rietk√∂tter Brewing House, Mutter Wittig, the Friedrich Lueg Haus, the Schlegel Tower, the Jahrhunderthalle building, etc.
